    {
      "id": "b186dfe9_eac98844",
      "file_path": "participant/participant-impl/participant-impl-policy/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/clamp/controlloop/participant/policy/main/handler/ControlLoopElementHandler.java",
      "patchset_number": 4,
      "line": 123,
      "message": "I wanted to have this discussion when Liam is back. As per wiki, we need to pass ControlLoopElementDefinition (Or in Tosca terms ToscaNodeTemplate) alone instead of passing complete ToscaServiceTemplate to every ControlLoopElement. \nBut, When it comes to Policy ControlLoopElement, \"policies\" and \"policy-types\" doesnot reside under ToscaNodeTemplate, They are either siblings to ToscaNodeTemplate or siblings of ToscaTopologyTemplate. \nFor this reason, As a stop gap solution, to unblock Policy Participant work that is being done in https://jira.onap.org/browse/POLICY-3508 I had to keep the interface as it is, and get the ToscaServiceTemplate with a new API below.\nToscaServiceTemplate controlLoopDefinition = intermediaryApi.getToscaServiceTemplate();\n\nThis needs a discussion to either reorganize ToscaServiceTemplate Or update the interfaces accordingly. A subtask created https://jira.onap.org/browse/POLICY-3541 under a new refactoring story https://jira.onap.org/browse/POLICY-3540 for keeping track of this issue",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7504,
        "name": "Sirisha Manchikanti",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "sirisha.manchikanti@est.tech",
        "username": "Sirisha_Manchikanti"
      },
      "updated": "2021-08-18 12:02:31.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "2da16719_72d361e2",
      "unresolved": false
    },
